            <packagedElement xmi:type="uml:Class" xmi:id="_lxWk4KyXEeyB76_OUW-bXg" name="ClientSendKnownConnectionsMsg">
              <ownedComment xmi:id="_qqZ-iKyXEeyB76_OUW-bXg">
                <body>One of the two message types used to achieve the auto-connect back feature.

A message type sent from a &quot;client&quot; to a &quot;host&quot; and a message of this type contains a set of 
INamedConnections that the client knows. 

The &quot;client&quot; is defined as the entity whose &quot;Get Selected Endpoint&quot; button is clicked on discovery server, 
and the &quot;host&quot; is entity that the &quot;client&quot; tries to connect to.

When receiving this message, its command will add the additional set of peers 
received to its existing set of peers, and send this new set to all peers in this new set.</body>
              </ownedComment>
              <ownedAttribute xmi:id="_qqVGAKyXEeyB76_OUW-bXg" name="serialVersionUID" visibility="private" isLeaf="true" isStatic="true" isReadOnly="true">
                <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType" href="pathmap://UML_LIBRARIES/JavaPrimitiveTypes.library.uml#long"/>
