            <packagedElement xmi:type="uml:Class" xmi:id="_lxWk4qyXEeyB76_OUW-bXg" name="HostSendKnownConnectionsMsg">
              <ownedComment xmi:id="_qqZ-iqyXEeyB76_OUW-bXg">
                <body>One of the two message types used to achieve the auto-connect back feature.

A message type sent from a &quot;host&quot;. This message contains a set of INamedConnections
that the host knows. The &quot;host&quot; is defined as the entity that receives IClientSendKnownConnectionsMsg.

When receiving this message, its command will update its set of peers.</body>
              </ownedComment>
              <ownedAttribute xmi:id="_qqWUIqyXEeyB76_OUW-bXg" name="serialVersionUID" visibility="private" isLeaf="true" isStatic="true" isReadOnly="true">
